{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17639645","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17639645"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T19:08:57+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T19:08:57+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17787"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"17787","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/17787"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.65,0.13,0,0.1,0.13]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10501"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"74907"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10501","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10501"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17787"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"60405"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"12"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"34"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"163"},{"type":"tags","id":"260"},{"type":"tags","id":"1903"},{"type":"tags","id":"2843"},{"type":"tags","id":"2860"},{"type":"tags","id":"4931"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"5810"},{"type":"tags","id":"8133"},{"type":"tags","id":"10221"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"24504"},{"type":"contributions","id":"24508"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"74907","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/74907"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 55-year-old man presents to the General Practice clinic with a two-day history of acute onset pain and swelling in his right knee. He has a history of hypertension and hyperlipidaemia, for which he takes Lisinopril and Atorvastatin. He denies any history of recent trauma or fever. On examination, he appears well. His pulse rate is 78/min, blood pressure 130/85 mmHg, respiratory rate 16/min, SpO2 98% on room air, and temperature 37.0\u00b0C. The right knee is swollen, warm, and tender with a reduced range of motion.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following investigations will provide a definitive diagnosis?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Arthrocentesis","X-ray of the knee","Blood cultures","Serum uric acid level","MRI of the knee"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EArthrocentesis\u003C/strong\u003E is the definitive investigation for differentiating between septic arthritis, gout, and pseudogout. By aspirating synovial fluid from the affected joint, clinicians can analyse the fluid for the presence of crystals, white blood cells, and bacteria. This analysis can confirm the diagnosis of gout (urate crystals), pseudogout (calcium pyrophosphate crystals), or septic arthritis (bacterial infection).\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EX-ray of the knee\u003C/strong\u003E can show joint effusion or chronic changes associated with gout or pseudogout, but it cannot definitively diagnose an acute episode or differentiate between these conditions.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EBlood cultures\u003C/strong\u003E may be positive in cases of septic arthritis, especially if the infection is systemic, but they are not definitive for diagnosing joint-specific conditions like gout or pseudogout.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESerum uric acid level\u003C/strong\u003E can be elevated in gout, but it is not definitive as levels can be normal during an acute attack or elevated in asymptomatic individuals.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMRI of the knee\u003C/strong\u003E can provide detailed images of joint structures and may show inflammation or effusion, but it does not provide a definitive diagnosis of the underlying cause of joint inflammation.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Arthrocentesis is the definitive investigation for differentiating between septic arthritis, gout, and pseudogout.","Analysis of synovial fluid can identify the presence of crystals or infection, aiding in accurate diagnosis."],"references":["Puebla DL, Farrow RA. Ultrasound-Guided Arthrocentesis. [Updated 2023 Jul 24]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK573084/","Kouranloo K, Christie J. Acute hot joints on the medical take: tapping into skills of the workforce. Clin Med (Lond). 2023 Nov;23(Suppl 6):86. doi: 10.7861/clinmed.23-6-s86. PMID: 38182207; PMCID: PMC11046624.","Roth CA, Da Lomba T, Dadwani R, Dahm J, Strelzow J. Analysis of factors that drives arthrocentesis for suspected septic joint. Ther Adv Musculoskelet Dis. 2021 Apr 22;13:1759720X211002582. doi: 10.1177/1759720X211002582. PMID: 33995601; PMCID: PMC8072930.","Fenando A, Rednam M, Gujarathi R, et al. Gout. [Updated 2024 Feb 12]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK546606/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"60405"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17787"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"60405","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/60405"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-28T09:36:52+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-28T09:37:21+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10501"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"74907"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"12","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/12"},"attr